You are an unwitting yet gleeful exemplary of those what wrought modern society as consequence of their eternally-unacknowledged faults.

@The_Wangus Now, if you want to get deeper: I personally don't dislike GRRM, not because he is full of himself, but because he is empty of anything real, an utter nihilistic pervy hack fantasy writer, whose whole MO is attempting to subvert high-fantasy... And he realized about 60% of the way through that its easy to start nihilism, easy to stir up drama and salacious interest, and much harder to finish, especially when you're writing fantasy... So instead, he ran off to do some assorted irrelevant slop to avoid finishing the main plot, knowing that endpoint would tank his career. 
And here we are, talking about the goi-slop mass-media adaptation - a meager one at that - which is being fellated by rubes on the basis that its SLIGHTLY LESS SHIT than the literal turds we've been getting hoisted before us.

Someone legit said to me in these comments "this show is the antithesis of modern television", and I just about shat brown water laughing, each time being driven by my incredulity back to take another peek. 😂

@bankaijd55 I dunno, I disagree - I felt the dialogue was choppy and often very inorganic, and the pacing felt extremely rushed, in a very weird way no less.

And yeah, I mean, if you wanted to do this right, its clear how you'd go about doing it.
Rushing through it for the sake of making it a 3.5 hours mini-series is just... Weird. Its like trying to turn the Hobbit into a 3-movie story; like, just, why? It doesn't make any sense and undermines what you're nominally trying to do... Just very frustrating, its like modern media production is a complete shitshow and nobody seems to understand how that negatively impacts narrative.

